**Big Picture Context:** SCVS is a community-driven framework for software supply chain assurance, reducing risks from attacks like SolarWinds. Supports Biden EO 14028, NIST SSDF PW.9 (Produce Well-Secured Software). Goals: Authenticity, integrity, safety of components.
**Core Concepts:** Software Supply Chain (code origin to distribution); Supply Chain Attack (target weak links); SBOM (nested inventory with metadata: versions, licenses, vendors, hashes); Component Verification (authenticity checks).
**6 Control Families (V1-V6):**
- **V1 Inventory:** Complete list of direct/transitive components. Practices: Automated scanning (OWASP Dependency-Check), track versions/licenses.
- **V2 SBOM:** Machine-readable formal record (CycloneDX/SPDX). Practices: Generate at build time, include relationships/supplier data.
- **V3 Build Environment:** Reproducible, secure builds. Practices: Isolated envs (Docker), no external fetches, hardened tools, tamper-evident logs.
- **V4 Sign &amp; Verify:** Cryptographic signing of artifacts/binaries. Practices: Use cosign/Sigstore, verify before integration, short-lived keys/HSMs.
- **V5 Publish &amp; Distribute:** Secure release of signed artifacts/SBOMs. Practices: Trusted registries (e.g., Sigstore), SLSA provenance metadata.
- **V6 Operate &amp; Monitor:** Post-deploy scanning/monitoring. Practices: Continuous vuln scans (Dependabot), EOSL tracking, incident response.
